{"key":"processedPost-19680953","value":{"id":19680953,"first":19679970,"last":19682580,"when":1394568462,"utime":"03/11/14 11:07 PM","content":"Definitely the spawn, and if you try to keep fruiting them with the mold, the problem will get worse.&nbsp; There may be trich spores nearly everywhere, but not in the numbers they are after a bloom indoors.&nbsp; This makes it hard to produce clean grain spawn.<br /><br />I'd move the tub outdoors to finish if mold is showing this early.&nbsp; On future tubs, try to make the substrate a bit drier.&nbsp; The mycelium will colonize a <i>lightly moist</i> substrate much faster than a damp or wet one. Then, put the moisture for fruiting in by soaking an hour or so after full colonization. <br /><br />I've gone as low as 1:10 on spawn ratio using this method and still get colonized in ten to fourteen days or so.<br />RR","title":"Re: long spawn runs"}}